Title: Object: Cléopâtre qui montre à Auguste le buste de Jules César
Description: Cleopatra showing the bust of Caesar to Augustus, after Battoni; the queen of Egypt is seen sitting at centre, half-length; she takes the hand of Augustus, who stands on the left, and gestures towards the bust of Caesar which is standing on a table at right Etching and engraving
Curator's comments: After a painting now in the Musée des Beaux-arts, Dijon; see Clark, 1985, cat. No.252.
